humanMachineDialogue.author: Memory Reasoning
humanMachineDialogue.text: Based on the information provided in the pathology report, there is no mention of any positive lymph nodes or metastases in the sentinel or regional lymph nodes. Therefore, according to the new rules 10 and 11, the N stage for this patient's cancer is N0.

humanMachineDialogue.author: ZS Reasoning
humanMachineDialogue.text: The pathology report does not mention any involvement of regional lymph nodes (axillary, internal mammary, or supraclavicular lymph nodes) by cancer cells. The absence of lymph node involvement supports the N0 stage. The T stage (pT1c) provided in the report refers to the size of the primary tumor, and it does not affect the N stage in this context.
